WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.298
The FX original series,
The Americans.

00:03.330 --> 00:05.628
The new season,
Wednesdays at 10:00 on FX.

00:08.840 --> 00:10.159
PREVIOUSLY ON
"THE AMERICANS"...

00:10.210 --> 00:12.371
MY MOTHER...SHE'S DYING.

00:12.410 --> 00:14.799
I WANT TO ARRANGE A TRIP
FOR ELIZABETH TO SEE HER MOTHER

00:14.840 --> 00:16.148
ONE LAST TIME.

00:16.180 --> 00:20.139
SHE HAD A REAL SPIRIT,
LIKE YOURS.

00:20.180 --> 00:22.148
HOW CAN I BELIEVE

00:22.190 --> 00:24.511
ANYTHING YOU SAY?

00:24.550 --> 00:26.654
WE WANT A PIECE OF WHATEVER
IT IS YOU GOT GOING ON

00:26.690 --> 00:28.385
WITH YOUR FRIEND
THE CONSULTANT.

00:28.420 --> 00:29.978
I'M SURE HE WOULD
LOVE TO KNOW

00:30.030 --> 00:31.657
WHAT'S GOING ON
AT NORTHROP, TOO.

00:31.690 --> 00:33.328
I.S.I. IS SENDING SOMEONE
IMPORTANT TO MEET THE CIA.

00:33.360 --> 00:34.896
MUJAHIDEEN.

00:34.930 --> 00:37.194
Yousaf: 10 DAYS AGO,
THE CIA ASKED US TO GIVE THEM

00:37.230 --> 00:38.993
THE NAMES OF
THE MUJAHIDEEN COMMANDERS

00:39.030 --> 00:41.692
WITH THE BEST LANGUAGE SKILLS.

00:41.740 --> 00:44.607
THEY FLY 3 OF THEM HERE
ON THE 18th.

00:50.280 --> 00:53.249
[ MACHINES WHIRRING ]

00:53.280 --> 00:56.283
[ WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ]

01:11.230 --> 01:13.437
Man in distance: YEAH, YEAH.
[ SPEAKS INDISTINCT LY ]

01:50.340 --> 01:54.174
[ DIAL TONE DRONING ]

01:59.280 --> 02:00.918
[ CLICK ]

02:00.950 --> 02:02.588
WOMAN: I just think that
G.W. isn't as strong a school.

02:02.620 --> 02:03.985
[ CLICK ]

02:04.020 --> 02:06.079
[ CLICK]
MAN: Try the basement.

02:06.120 --> 02:09.089
If it's not there,
I put it in the --
[ CLICK]

02:09.120 --> 02:10.781
[ CLICK]
WOMAN: ...on weekdays, sir.

02:10.830 --> 02:12.752
[ CLICK ]

02:12.800 --> 02:14.927
[ CLICK]
MAN: The idiot had his TV
turned up, and I didn't --

02:14.960 --> 02:16.598
[ CLICK ]

02:16.630 --> 02:17.995
[ CLICK, DIAL TONE DRONES ]

02:18.030 --> 02:19.292
YEAH, I'M TRYING TO GET THROUGH
TO HOUSEKEEPING.

02:19.340 --> 02:21.638
THIS IS HOUSEKEEPING.

02:21.670 --> 02:23.638
I NEED MORE PILLOWS
IN ROOM 629.

02:23.670 --> 02:25.604
CHECK THE TOP
OF THE CLOSET.

02:25.640 --> 02:26.834
THANK YOU.

02:26.880 --> 02:28.199
[ HANGS UP RECEIVER ]

02:45.490 --> 02:47.299
[ TV PLAYING INDISTINCTLY ]

02:47.330 --> 02:49.195
Philip: HELLO?

02:49.230 --> 02:50.527
HEY, DAD.

02:50.570 --> 02:52.197
HEY!

02:52.240 --> 02:53.798
Man on TV: ...CONNECTING
CABLES, JACK, PLUG...

02:53.840 --> 02:55.535
WHERE'S YOUR SISTER?

02:55.570 --> 02:57.003
...ACCESSORIES ARE ALSO
IN STOCK FOR YOUR CONVENIENCE.

02:57.040 --> 02:59.031
SHE LEFI' A NOTE IN THE KITCHEN.

02:59.070 --> 03:00.708
MM.
[ SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ]

03:00.740 --> 03:04.301
GUEST SPEAKER AT THE CHURCH.

03:04.350 --> 03:08.969
SHE'S STAYING THE NIGHT
AT PASTOR TIM'S AFI'ERWARDS.

03:09.020 --> 03:11.318
SAYS WHO?
SAYS HER.

03:11.350 --> 03:12.988
IS THERE A NUMBER?

03:13.020 --> 03:14.988
* WHATEVER YOU WANT
AT DELMONT *

03:15.020 --> 03:17.887
* WHATEVER
YOU WANT AT DELMONT *

03:17.930 --> 03:19.693
[ DIALING TELEPHONE ]

03:19.730 --> 03:21.049
Man on TV: THE WAR IS OVER.

03:21.100 --> 03:22.499
M.A.S.H. IS FINALLY GOING HOME.

03:22.530 --> 03:25.021
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

03:25.070 --> 03:26.560
IT'S A MACHINE.

03:26.600 --> 03:28.830
HI, TIM, ALICE.
THIS IS PHILIP JENNINGS.

03:28.870 --> 03:30.235
WE JUST GOT PAIGE'S NOTE.

03:30.270 --> 03:32.534
COULD YOU HAVE HER CALL US?
THANKS.

03:32.580 --> 03:34.673
WE SHOULD GO OVER THERE.

03:34.710 --> 03:37.178
I'LL GO.
NO. WE SHOULD BOTH GO.

03:37.210 --> 03:38.677
WE DON'T KNOW WHAT
WE'RE DEALING WITH.

03:38.710 --> 03:41.019
WE'RE JUST GONNA PICK UP PAIGE.

03:41.050 --> 03:42.347
OKAY.

03:42.390 --> 03:43.846
LIGHTS OUT AT 10:00, HENRY.

03:43.890 --> 03:45.915
Man: TUNE IN ON MONDAY
AT 8:30 PM.

03:45.950 --> 03:47.713
FOR THE 2 1/2-HOUR
TELEVISION FINALE...
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

03:47.760 --> 03:49.523
Hawkeye: IF YOU'LL CALL ME
A TAXI, I'LL BE ON MY WAY.

03:49.560 --> 03:53.428
Man: ...ONLY ON CHANNEL 5.

03:53.460 --> 03:57.419
***

03:57.470 --> 04:00.439
-- Captions by VITAC --

04:31.300 --> 04:35.236
[ DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE ]

04:35.270 --> 04:37.909
WHAT TIME IS IT?

04:37.940 --> 04:39.237
9:46.

04:39.270 --> 04:40.771
WHERE THE HELL ARE THEY?

04:40.810 --> 04:43.745
I DON'T KNOW. HOW LONG DOES
A CHURCH LECTURE GO?

04:43.780 --> 04:45.407
YOU'RE ASKING ME?

04:45.450 --> 04:46.917
PROBABLY TURNED INTO

04:46.950 --> 04:51.614
SOME POTLUCK,
POSTER-MAKING SING-ALONG.

04:53.620 --> 04:55.178
[ VEHICLE APPROACHES ]

04:56.460 --> 04:57.984
DON'T JUMP ALL OVER HER.

04:58.030 --> 04:59.588
WHAT?
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

04:59.630 --> 05:01.257
NO, MAYBE I DON'T.

05:01.300 --> 05:05.088
YOU WANNA TEACH ME HOW
TO HANDLE MY OWN DAUGHTER?

05:05.130 --> 05:08.998
[ CAR DOORS CLOSE ]

05:11.870 --> 05:13.599
HI.
HEY.

05:13.640 --> 05:17.269
HEY, GUYS. EVERYTHING OKAY?

05:17.310 --> 05:20.677
YEAH. WE JUST DIDN'T KNOW PAIGE
WAS COMING OVER TONIGHT, SO...

05:20.720 --> 05:22.483
I LEFI' A NOTE.
UH, YOU DID,

05:22.520 --> 05:24.283
BUT YOU SHOULD'VE --
IT'S THE MIDDLE OF THE WEEK,
PAIGE.

05:24.320 --> 05:26.185
WELL, I DID ALL MY HOMEWORK.

05:26.220 --> 05:30.281
THAT'S NOT THE POINT.
YOU CAN'T JUST RUN OFF.

05:30.330 --> 05:33.128
UH, I'M SORRY. WE HAD NO IDEA.

05:33.160 --> 05:36.152
WELL, I'M SORRY, BUT I HAVE
ALL MY STUFF FOR SCHOOL.

05:36.200 --> 05:37.497
I'M STAYING.

05:37.530 --> 05:39.361
NO, YOU'RE NOT, PAIGE.

05:40.900 --> 05:42.629
PAIGE, COME ON. THEY'RE RIGHT.

05:42.670 --> 05:44.467
WE THOUGHT THEY KNEW.
THEY DIDN'T.

05:44.510 --> 05:46.330
I'LL GET YOUR BAG.

05:46.380 --> 05:48.200
[ SIGHS ]

05:48.240 --> 05:50.208
AH, I'M REALLY SORRY, GUYS.

05:50.250 --> 05:52.002
[ CHUCKLES ] HEY.

05:52.050 --> 05:55.178
UH, THANK YOU
FOR SENDING OVER THOSE RATES

05:55.220 --> 05:57.142
FOR THE TRIP TO KENYA.
I JUST -- I SAW 'EM TODAY.

05:57.190 --> 05:59.488
IT'S VERY REASONABLE.
YEAH, THERE'S
A COUPLE OF CARRIERS

05:59.520 --> 06:01.659
OFFERING GOOD DEALS TO AFRICA
RIGHT NOW.

06:01.690 --> 06:03.157
GOOD.
HERE YOU GO.

06:03.190 --> 06:04.987
[ SPEAKS INDISTINCT LY ]
Alice: [Whispers] BYE.

06:05.030 --> 06:08.420
WELL, AGAIN, UM, SORRY FOR
THE MISUNDERSTANDING.

06:11.370 --> 06:12.860
Philip: GOOD NIGHT.

06:12.900 --> 06:14.868
Alice: GOOD NIGHT.

06:43.600 --> 06:46.933
[ TURNS OFF ENGINE,
SHIFTS GEARS ]

06:46.970 --> 06:49.564
HOLD IT.

06:49.610 --> 06:50.861
[ PUSHES BU'I'I'ON ]

06:50.910 --> 06:55.700
[ WHIRRING ]

06:55.740 --> 06:57.048
[ WHIRRING STOPS ]

06:57.080 --> 06:58.900
THAT WAS NOT OKAY.

06:58.950 --> 07:00.372
GOING TO A LECTURE?

07:00.420 --> 07:03.048
YOU THINK TNHCJS IS A GAME?

07:03.090 --> 07:05.445
YOU CAN'T RUN OFF LIKE THAT.
WE NEED TO BE ABLE TO TRUST YOU.

07:05.490 --> 07:07.617
DID YOU SAY ANYTHING
TO PASTOR TIM?

07:07.660 --> 07:10.481
[ SCOFFS ] WHAT DO YOU THINK?

07:16.930 --> 07:18.591
YOU ASKED FOR THE TRUTH,
AND WITH THAT

07:18.630 --> 07:20.632
COMES RESPONSIBILITY.
DO YOU UNDERSTAND THAT?

07:23.440 --> 07:25.169
PAIGE.

07:26.810 --> 07:28.903
YOU NEED TO TELL US
YOU UNDERSTAND.

07:28.940 --> 07:31.909
SO, WHAT? I CAN'T SEE
PASTOR TIM ANYMORE?

07:31.950 --> 07:33.611
NO, NO ONE IS SAYING THAT.

07:33.650 --> 07:35.572
YOU NEED TO ACT AS IF
EVERYTHING IS PERFECT LY NORMAL.

07:35.620 --> 07:37.087
BUT IT'S NOT.
PAIGE.

07:37.120 --> 07:40.351
I DIDN'T TELL HIM.

07:42.660 --> 07:45.026
[ SIGHS ]

07:47.200 --> 07:48.451
CAN I GET BY?

07:55.140 --> 07:57.301
[ DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES ]

07:57.340 --> 08:00.832
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

08:00.880 --> 08:03.144
YOU HAVE TO GO
TO MARTHA'S TONIGHT, RIGHT?

08:03.180 --> 08:05.978
[ SIGHS ] YEAH.

08:11.190 --> 08:12.817
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

08:14.690 --> 08:17.488
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

08:17.530 --> 08:22.820
[ MAN IN DISTANCE
SPEAKING INDISTINCT LY ]

08:31.240 --> 08:33.970
Woman: YEAH.

08:34.010 --> 08:37.173
Man: IS THAT A PARKING SPOT?
[ MAN SPEAKS INDISTINCT LY ]

08:38.510 --> 08:40.876
I KEEP THINKING I WANNA PAINT --

08:40.920 --> 08:42.808
BLUE OR SOMETHING BOLDER.

08:42.850 --> 08:45.648
BUT THEN YOU HAVE TO LIVE
WITH IT.

08:45.690 --> 08:48.659
AND THE SMELL --
IT LINGERS, YOU KNOW.

08:48.690 --> 08:51.488
MUCH LONGER THAN THEY SAY.

08:51.530 --> 08:54.328
HMM, IT'S A NICE PLACE.

08:54.360 --> 08:56.828
THANK YOU.

08:56.870 --> 08:58.064
IT'S HOME.

08:58.100 --> 09:01.228
LOOK, I'M SORRY TO DROP BY
UNANNOUNCED.

09:01.270 --> 09:05.536
JUST...SO HARD TO TALK
AROUND THE OFFICE THESE DAYS.

09:05.570 --> 09:08.835
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]
TELL ME ABOUT IT.

09:08.880 --> 09:15.069
I SAW YOU TODAY STARING
INTO YOUR COFFEE MUG

09:15.120 --> 09:18.385
FOR A MINUTE, STRAIGHT.

09:20.720 --> 09:23.257
YOU KNOW I TALK TO IT
SOMETIMES,

09:23.290 --> 09:25.178
AND I BEG IT
TO WAKE ME UP.

09:25.230 --> 09:27.926
[ CHUCKLES ]
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:27.960 --> 09:30.190
YOU JUST SEEMED A LITTLE
DISTRACT ED TO ME, MARTHA.

09:30.230 --> 09:32.528
I WANTED TO MAKE SURE
YOU'RE OKAY.

09:32.570 --> 09:36.563
ME? I'M FINE.
UH...IT'S JUST HECTIC,

09:36.610 --> 09:38.737
WITH AGENT TAFFET THERE.

09:38.770 --> 09:40.909
AGENT GAAD'S SCHEDULE IS...
[ CLA'I'I'ER ]

09:40.940 --> 09:42.100
EXHAUSTING.

09:42.140 --> 09:43.698
HMM.

09:43.750 --> 09:47.413
WE ALL KNOW IT'S THE SECRETARIES
THAT MAKE THE PLACE RUN.

09:47.450 --> 09:50.283
THAT'S NICE. THANK YOU.

09:50.320 --> 09:52.959
YOU DON'T ALWAYS GET
THE CREDIT YOU DESERVE.

09:59.430 --> 10:03.423
I READ THAT.
THAT'S A GOOD BOOK.

10:06.970 --> 10:10.167
WHAT ARE YOU, UH...
DOING HERE, STAN?

10:11.940 --> 10:14.909
I HEAR THE GOSSIP AT WORK
ABOUT YOUR MARRIAGE...

10:14.940 --> 10:17.101
NO, NO, NO.
AND, YOU KNOW, YOU SHOULD
TALK TO SOMEBODY.

10:17.150 --> 10:19.971
BUT I'M NOT THE RIGHT PERSON.
NO, I JUST...

10:21.650 --> 10:24.244
I JUST WANTED YOU TO KNOW
WITH THINGS AT WORK,

10:24.290 --> 10:26.952
IF THERE'S ANYTHING
ON YOUR MIND,

10:26.990 --> 10:29.311
YOU CAN ALWAYS COME
TO ME.

10:31.130 --> 10:32.483
OKAY.

10:32.530 --> 10:35.158
I APPRECIATE THAT,
AGENT BEEMAN.

10:36.970 --> 10:38.824
YOU KNOW, I HAVE
AN EARLY MORNING,

10:38.870 --> 10:40.792
AND IT'S GETTING LATE.

10:40.840 --> 10:43.263
YEAH.

10:43.310 --> 10:47.178
YEAH. OKAY.

10:51.310 --> 10:52.971
[ LOCK CLICKS ]

10:56.220 --> 10:58.347
I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW.

10:58.390 --> 10:59.948
YES, YOU WILL.

10:59.990 --> 11:01.184
GOOD NIGHT.

11:01.220 --> 11:02.517
GOOD NIGHT.

11:36.730 --> 11:38.857
[ SIGHS ]

11:46.700 --> 11:47.997
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

11:48.040 --> 11:49.667
WHAT HAPPENED?

11:49.700 --> 11:51.668
HANS WAVED ME OFF.

11:51.710 --> 11:53.837
I MET HIM AFI'ER.
HE SAID HE SAW A GUY

11:53.880 --> 11:56.178
GET OUT OF A CAR
WITH GOVERNMENT PLATES

11:56.210 --> 11:58.075
GOING TO
HER APARTMENT BUILDING.

12:01.220 --> 12:02.369
[ SIGHS ]

12:02.420 --> 12:04.081
HAS SHE CALLED?

12:04.120 --> 12:06.884
TWO MESSAGES SO FAR.

12:12.090 --> 12:15.594
HANS DID GOOD.

12:15.630 --> 12:18.224
YEAH.

12:20.270 --> 12:22.568
WHAT NOW?

12:24.140 --> 12:26.301
I DON'T KNOW.

12:40.160 --> 12:43.288
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

12:48.600 --> 12:50.898
MISS HANSON?

12:50.930 --> 12:53.091
I'M A FRIEND
OF YOUR HUSBAND.

12:53.140 --> 12:56.632
CLARK KNOWS
YOU MUST BE WORRIED.

12:56.670 --> 12:58.467
IS HE ALL RIGHT?

12:58.510 --> 13:00.728
YES.

13:00.780 --> 13:03.408
[ DOOR HANDLE CLICKS ]

13:03.450 --> 13:07.170
[ ENGINE IDLING ]

13:22.300 --> 13:25.599
NICE AND EASY. YEAH?
AND JUST REMEMBER

13:25.630 --> 13:27.166
THAT THE LENS IS RIGHT THERE,
SO...

13:27.200 --> 13:29.088
THEY WON'T THINK
IT'S STRANGE

13:29.140 --> 13:31.267
TO SEE A WOMAN CARRYING
A PURSE ONTO THE PLANT FLOOR?

13:31.310 --> 13:33.005
I TAKE IT EVERY TIME
I LEAVE THE OFFICE.

13:33.040 --> 13:34.439
EVERY GIRL DOES.

13:34.480 --> 13:35.970
TAKE A LOT OF SHOTS.

13:36.010 --> 13:38.501
BETI'ER TO HAVE TOO MANY
THAN TOO FEW.

13:38.550 --> 13:40.438
WHAT'S HER EXCUSE
FOR BEING THERE?

13:40.480 --> 13:42.448
I'M GOING TO SEE
THE MATERIALS ENGINEER

13:42.480 --> 13:44.789
ABOUT THE MACHINE SETTINGS
ON HIS NEW PLANS.
THAT'S RIGHT.

13:44.820 --> 13:46.344
AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
SEARCH YOUR PURSE?

13:46.390 --> 13:48.858
BABY, DON'T WORRY.

13:48.890 --> 13:50.778
THE GUARDS ONLY CARE
ABOUT MY BADGE.

13:50.830 --> 13:52.786
MM. AND THEY WANT EVERY ANGLE,

13:52.830 --> 13:55.355
SO THEY SAID AN EASY WAY
TO DO THAT

13:55.400 --> 13:57.459
IS TO SPOT THE ENGINEER EARLY.

13:57.500 --> 13:59.695
START ONE WAY
AROUND THE FUSELAGE

13:59.730 --> 14:02.290
AND COME BACK THE OTHER WAY
IF YOU CAN.

14:02.340 --> 14:04.467
YOU KNOW,
IT'S JUST IF YOU CAN.

14:04.510 --> 14:05.909
OKAY.
AND ALSO...

14:11.250 --> 14:12.501
TAKE THIS.

14:12.550 --> 14:13.972
Maurice: WHAT IS THAT?

14:14.020 --> 14:16.989
IT'S A SEDATIVE. KEEP YOU CALM.

14:17.020 --> 14:18.647
SHE'S NOT TAKING THAT.

14:18.690 --> 14:21.887
IT'S 5 MILLIGRAMS. TRUST ME.
IT'S HELPFUL.

14:28.760 --> 14:30.660
I'LL MEET YOU AFTER
WHERE WE SAID.

14:30.700 --> 14:33.897
YOU'RE GONNA BE GREAT,
JUST LIKE YOU PRACTICED.

15:02.560 --> 15:03.868
MARTHA?

15:03.900 --> 15:07.233
[ CAR DEPARTS ]

15:07.270 --> 15:09.261
I'M SO SORRY
ABOUT LAST NIGHT.

15:09.300 --> 15:10.858
I TRIED CALLING YOU
FIVE TIMES.

15:10.910 --> 15:12.366
YES, I KNOW, I KNOW.

15:12.410 --> 15:14.037
WHAT AM I DOING HERE,
CLARK?

15:14.080 --> 15:16.947
AND WHO WAS THAT MAN?
HE -- HE'S A FRIEND.

15:16.980 --> 15:20.040
I COULDN'T BE CERTAIN
YOUR APARTMENT WAS SAFE.

15:20.080 --> 15:22.548
I-I CAME LAST NIGHT,

15:22.580 --> 15:25.413
BUT I SAW SOMEONE GO
INTO YOUR APARTMENT BUILDING,

15:25.450 --> 15:28.214
AND HE WAS DRIVING A CAR
WITH GOVERNMENT PLATES.

15:28.260 --> 15:30.558
IT WAS AGENT BEEMAN.

15:30.590 --> 15:32.751
WHAT DID HE WANT?

15:32.790 --> 15:36.419
HE SAID THAT HE WAS
WORRIED ABOUT ME, BUT...

15:36.460 --> 15:37.768
WHY? WHAT'D HE SAY?

15:37.800 --> 15:40.564
HE SAID IT'S TENSE
IN THE OFFICE

15:40.600 --> 15:42.898
AND WE CAN'T TALK,
AND IF I HAVE ANYTHING

15:42.940 --> 15:44.805
ON MY MIND,
THAT I SHOULD GO TO HIM.

15:47.140 --> 15:48.471
WHAT AM I GONNA DO,
CLARK?

15:48.510 --> 15:51.741
OKAY, MARTHA, LISTEN.
I-I...

15:51.780 --> 15:55.079
I DON'T KNOW QUITE HOW
TO SAY THIS.

15:55.120 --> 15:57.315
BUT WE MIGHT HAVE TO GO...

15:57.350 --> 16:00.808
A-AWAY SOMEPLACE NEW.

16:00.860 --> 16:03.249
CLARK, I --
IT'S GONNA --
IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.

16:03.290 --> 16:05.258
EVERYTHING'S GONNA BE OKAY.
I CAN'T JUST --

16:05.290 --> 16:07.429
JUST -- JUST -- JUST TRUST ME.
THEY DON'T KNOW.

16:07.460 --> 16:09.655
IF THEY DID, IT WOULD BE
A VERY DIFFERENT VISIT.

16:09.700 --> 16:11.167
THEY WOULD BE BUGGING
YOUR PHONE,

16:11.200 --> 16:12.929
SURVEILLING YOU 24 HOURS A DAY,
AND THEY WOULDN'T HAVE

16:12.970 --> 16:14.289
TIPPED YOU
BY SENDING AGENT BEEMAN.

16:14.340 --> 16:17.161
I -- MARTHA, I WILL FIGURE
THIS OUT.

16:17.210 --> 16:20.600
I WILL FIGURE THIS OUT.

16:20.640 --> 16:23.200
I PROMISE.

16:26.680 --> 16:31.117
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

16:31.150 --> 16:34.017
[ TELEPHONE RINGING
IN DISTANCE ]

16:34.060 --> 16:36.449
HEY, STAN.
UH, I'M LATE FOR A MEETING.

16:36.490 --> 16:37.821
ALL RIGHT,
MAYBE FIND ME LATER?

16:37.860 --> 16:39.282
ABOUT WHAT, EXACTLY?

16:39.330 --> 16:42.652
I'VE GOT A FEW MORE QUESTIONS
ABOUT NINA.

16:48.900 --> 16:51.664
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

16:53.340 --> 16:54.807
WHAT IS WITH YOU?

16:54.840 --> 16:56.205
I DON'T KNOW, STAN.

16:56.240 --> 16:58.470
THERE WAS SOMETHING
GOING ON WITH YOU AND NINA.

16:58.510 --> 17:00.341
THAT MUCH IS CLEAR TO ME.

17:02.850 --> 17:05.045
WHAT ARE YOU
ACCUSING ME OF?

17:05.090 --> 17:07.308
DID YOU PLANT THE BUG?

17:07.360 --> 17:10.523
NO.

17:10.560 --> 17:13.256
AND YOU ARE NOT
AS SMART AS YOU LOOK.

17:15.060 --> 17:18.689
YOU READ ALL THOSE FILES.

17:18.730 --> 17:21.893
LET'S SAY THE WOMAN I SHOT
DIDN'T ACTUALLY DIE.

17:21.940 --> 17:23.168
MAYBE SHE'S THE ONE

17:23.210 --> 17:25.201
WHO BEAT THE SHIT
OUT OF YOU AND GAAD.

17:25.240 --> 17:30.177
MAYBE SHE EVEN KILLED
MY PARTNER, CHRIS AMADOR.

17:30.210 --> 17:33.179
OUR OFFICE IS A TARGET
OF THE ILLEGALS.

17:33.220 --> 17:37.042
THE BEST, MOST DANGEROUS
OFFICERS THE K.G.B. HAS.

17:37.090 --> 17:38.387
NOW THEY GOT
TO SOMEBODY INSIDE,

17:38.420 --> 17:40.217
AND IT WASN'T ME.

17:40.260 --> 17:42.683
WORK ON THAT.

17:42.720 --> 17:47.396
[ WHIRRING ]

17:47.430 --> 17:49.728
[ BEEPS ]

17:49.760 --> 17:52.593
[TYPING ]
Man on tape: CAN'T YOU GO
IN THERE AND SAY SOMETHING?

17:52.630 --> 17:55.690
Man: ARE YOU KIDDING?
[ SPEAKS INDISTINCT LY ]

17:55.740 --> 17:57.708
[ BELL DINGS ]

17:57.740 --> 18:03.030
[ WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ]
OVER TAPE ]

18:03.080 --> 18:06.538
[ CONVERSATIONS OVERLAPPING ]

18:06.580 --> 18:11.279
[ KEYS CLACKING ]

18:24.670 --> 18:26.467
[ DOOR HANDLE CLICKS ]

18:32.010 --> 18:33.568
SHE DID HER JOB.

18:33.610 --> 18:35.407
THIS WASN'T THE ARRANGEMENT.

18:35.440 --> 18:37.271
I'M DEALING WITH
THIS SIDE OF THINGS NOW.

18:39.450 --> 18:40.917
GOT A PROBLEM WITH THAT?

18:40.950 --> 18:42.269
I DO.

18:43.650 --> 18:45.618
SUIT YOURSELF.

18:45.650 --> 18:47.618
THAT'S MY CAMERA.

18:50.490 --> 18:53.425
HOW ABOUT I TAKE
THE FILM OUT, EXPOSE IT,

18:53.460 --> 18:55.621
GIVE IT BACK TO YOU?

19:06.640 --> 19:08.130
[ZIP]

19:16.350 --> 19:18.386
[ZIP]

19:20.660 --> 19:23.959
TELL LISA I'LL TALK
TO HER SOON, IN PERSON.

19:23.990 --> 19:26.481
WHATEVER.

19:36.840 --> 19:38.569
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]
[ SPEAKS RUSSIAN ]

19:41.680 --> 19:43.033
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

19:46.050 --> 19:49.019
[ PEN SCRIBBLING ]

20:20.380 --> 20:23.508
WAS HER SENSE THAT STAN
WAS REALLY CONCERNED FOR HER

20:23.550 --> 20:25.518
OR THAT HE WAS
INVESTIGATING?

20:25.550 --> 20:28.189
SHE COULDN'T TELL.
SHE WAS UPSET, TERRIFIED.

20:28.220 --> 20:29.858
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

20:29.890 --> 20:31.426
I THINK STAN'S A NICE GUY,

20:31.460 --> 20:33.599
BUT HE'S NOT SHOWING UP
AT HIS SECRETARY'S APARTMENT

20:33.630 --> 20:35.257
OUT OF THE GOODNESS
OF HIS HEART.

20:35.300 --> 20:37.689
UNLESS HE'S LOOKING
FOR SOMETHING ELSE.

20:37.730 --> 20:39.027
WITH MARTHA?

20:39.070 --> 20:41.197
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

20:41.240 --> 20:43.196
YEAH?

20:43.240 --> 20:45.231
Philip: HEY.

20:47.310 --> 20:49.369
WHO ARE THESE PEOPLE?

20:49.410 --> 20:51.742
IS THIS ROGER, WHO WE WENT
TO SeaWorld WITH?

20:53.650 --> 20:55.049
YES.

20:55.080 --> 20:56.308
IS HE REALLY OUR COUSIN?

20:59.790 --> 21:02.111
SO THAT'S A LIE.

21:02.160 --> 21:03.889
PAIGE, THERE ARE GOING
TO BE THINGS THAT --

21:03.930 --> 21:06.387
AUNT HELEN, WHO YOU
STAYED WITH -- I MET HER.

21:06.430 --> 21:09.399
I WENT TO HER HOUSE.
WAS SHE REALLY SICK?

21:09.430 --> 21:10.761
IS SHE MY AUNT?

21:12.630 --> 21:14.962
WHO IS SHE?
IS SHE A RUSSIAN?

21:15.000 --> 21:16.399
CAN YOU PLEASE
KEEP YOUR VOICE DOWN?

21:16.440 --> 21:18.738
WHY?
BECAUSE HENRY IS JUST
DOWN THE HALL.

21:18.770 --> 21:20.738
OKAY, SO ROGER'S NOT
REALLY OUR COUSIN,

21:20.780 --> 21:23.806
HELEN'S NOT MY AUNT,
BUT HENRY IS MY BROTHER.

21:23.850 --> 21:25.272
IF YOU CALM DOWN
FOR A MINUTE, WE --

21:25.310 --> 21:26.777
YOU GUYS ARE MY PARENTS.
PAIGE, PLEASE, WE --

21:26.810 --> 21:28.744
BUT EVERYTHING ELSE
IS JUST A LIE, RIGHT?

21:28.780 --> 21:31.988
EVERYTHING IS A LIE!
PLEASE DON'T TOUCH ME.

21:32.020 --> 21:33.612
DON'T TOUCH ME.

21:37.660 --> 21:39.787
[ SIGHS ]

21:39.830 --> 21:41.957
PAIGE...

21:43.300 --> 21:45.791
[ DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES ]

22:03.150 --> 22:05.141
[ SNIFFLES ]

22:08.490 --> 22:10.685
[ SWALLOWS, EXHALES ]

22:20.840 --> 22:23.331
[ DIAL TONE DRONES ]

22:23.370 --> 22:27.807
[ DIALING ]

22:27.840 --> 22:29.068
[ EXHALES ]

22:32.680 --> 22:37.640
HI, MOM. HOW ARE YOU GUYS?

22:37.690 --> 22:39.419
IS DAD GETTING ON THE OTHER --

22:41.060 --> 22:42.652
HI, DADDY.

22:42.690 --> 22:47.821
OH, NOTHING. UM, I JUST WANTED
TO HEAR YOUR VOICES.

22:47.860 --> 22:52.365
NO, NO. [ SNIFFLES ]
SAME OLD, YOU KNOW.

22:52.400 --> 22:54.994
THE GLAMOROUS FBI.

22:55.040 --> 22:57.099
HE'S GREAT.

22:58.710 --> 23:00.701
NO, NOT RIGHT NOW. [ SNIFFLES ]

23:00.740 --> 23:04.574
WORK, WORK, WORK.
YOU KNOW HOW HE IS.

23:04.610 --> 23:06.749
NOTHING'S WRONG, MOM.

23:06.780 --> 23:10.238
IT'S JUST --
IT'S HARD SOMETIMES.

23:12.550 --> 23:15.383
I KNOW.

23:15.420 --> 23:17.183
OH, GOD. I HAVE...

23:17.220 --> 23:19.586
21 DAYS SAVED UP, BUT, UH,

23:19.630 --> 23:22.224
I DON'T WANNA LEAVE RIGHT NOW.

23:24.270 --> 23:26.522
I KNOW YOU ARE.

23:26.570 --> 23:28.868
I'M FINE.

23:28.900 --> 23:31.607
LET'S TALK ABOUT SOMETHING ELSE.

23:31.640 --> 23:36.407
UM, WHAT ARE YOU GUYS GONNA DO
FOR YOUR ANNIVERSARY?

23:39.410 --> 23:41.071
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

23:41.120 --> 23:43.372
[ DOOR OPENS ]

23:43.420 --> 23:45.285
HEY.

23:47.460 --> 23:48.916
[ CLOSES DOOR ]

23:59.770 --> 24:01.931
[ SIGHS ]

24:04.440 --> 24:07.773
[ CLICKS TEETH ]
THERE IS NO AUNT HELEN.

24:11.280 --> 24:14.078
YOUR MOM WASN'T...WELL,

24:14.120 --> 24:15.815
AND SHE NEEDED TIME
TO RECOVER,

24:15.850 --> 24:17.613
TO GET BETTER.

24:21.360 --> 24:23.954
IT'S NOT ALL A LIE,
PAIGE.

24:32.630 --> 24:37.090
THIS IS YOU IN THE HOSPITAL
THE NIGHT HENRY WAS BORN.

24:37.140 --> 24:38.459
YOUR MOM SAID I HAD
TO BRING YOU OVER THAT NIGHT,

24:38.510 --> 24:39.807
EVEN THOUGH IT WAS LATE.

24:39.840 --> 24:43.640
COULDN'T WAIT
TILL THE NEXT DAY.

24:43.680 --> 24:48.014
AND THIS IS
WHEN WE WENT CAMPING

24:48.050 --> 24:50.177
IN THE BLUE RIDGE MOUNTAINS.

24:50.220 --> 24:51.812
YOU WERE 7.

24:51.850 --> 24:54.353
SHARED A TENT WITH HENRY.

24:56.390 --> 24:59.188
HE WAS AFRAID
A BEAR WAS GONNA EAT HIM.

24:59.230 --> 25:02.529
I DIDN'T KNOW THAT.

25:02.560 --> 25:06.724
HE MADE ME PROMISE
NOT TO TELL.

25:13.510 --> 25:18.903
[ MAN AND WOMAN
SPEAKING RUSSIAN ]

26:24.310 --> 26:26.540
[ SHIFTS GEARS,
TURNS OFF ENGINE ]

26:26.580 --> 26:29.777
YOU SHOULD GO
AND TAKE HER WITH YOU.

26:32.150 --> 26:33.412
I DON'T KNOW.

26:33.450 --> 26:34.951
SHE DOESN'T THINK
SHE HAS ANY FAMILY,

26:34.990 --> 26:36.287
AND SHE DOES.

26:36.320 --> 26:40.051
LOOK, IF YOU DON'T TAKE HER,
I WILL.

26:40.090 --> 26:42.422
[ DOOR HANDLE CLICKS ]

26:46.630 --> 26:48.769
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

26:48.800 --> 26:50.267
Woman: EXCUSE ME.

26:55.010 --> 26:57.137
HI. I'M HERE
FOR ABASSIN ZADRAN.

26:57.180 --> 26:59.102
IT'S LATE.

26:59.150 --> 27:01.778
YEAH, I GOTTA TALK TO HIM
ABOUT TOMORROW'S MEETING.

27:04.520 --> 27:07.080
WAIT HERE.
SURE.

27:07.120 --> 27:09.315
I GOT SOMEONE HERE
WHO NEEDS CLEARANCE,

27:09.360 --> 27:10.782
PICKING UP ZADRAN.

27:10.830 --> 27:12.752
OKAY, CHECK IT OUT.

27:12.790 --> 27:15.293
IT'LL BE A MINUTE.

27:15.330 --> 27:18.128
SURE.

27:19.700 --> 27:21.497
[ DIAL TONE DRONES ]

27:21.540 --> 27:24.509
[ DIALS ]

27:24.540 --> 27:26.758
[ LINE RINGS, CLICK ]

27:26.810 --> 27:28.107
Security.

27:28.140 --> 27:30.131
I HAVE AN OFFICER HERE
FOR ABASSIN ZADRAN.

27:30.180 --> 27:31.602
NEED APPROVAL TO RELEASE HIM.

27:31.650 --> 27:33.538
HOLD THE LINE.

27:38.490 --> 27:41.948
YOU HAVE APPROVAL
TO RELEASE ABASSIN ZADRAN

27:41.990 --> 27:46.120
to the officer
with the ID number 24765.

27:46.160 --> 27:47.821
GOT IT.

27:49.160 --> 27:50.388
HE'S GOOD.

27:58.570 --> 28:00.333
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

28:00.370 --> 28:03.476
THIS IS LAURA GERING
OF THE CIA.

28:03.510 --> 28:05.842
GOOD EVENING.

28:05.880 --> 28:09.338
IS IT OKAY IF WE DRIVE
SOMEPLACE MORE PRIVATE?

28:09.380 --> 28:12.019
PLEASE.

28:12.050 --> 28:14.814
THE SENATORS ON THE COMMITTEE
ARE WORRIED.

28:14.860 --> 28:16.316
THEY DON'T THINK THEY CAN TRUST
THE MUJAHIDEEN

28:16.360 --> 28:18.328
WITH PORTABLE
ANTI-AIRCRAFT WEAPONS.

28:18.360 --> 28:20.658
THAT IS WHY WE ARE HERE --
TO CONVINCE THEM.

28:20.690 --> 28:22.726
THAT WAS THE HOPE.

28:22.760 --> 28:24.728
HOW WELL DO YOU KNOW
THE MEN YOU TRAVELED WITH?

28:24.770 --> 28:28.160
NOT WELL, BUT WE WANT
THE SAME THING.

28:28.200 --> 28:30.339
THEY'RE BOTH FROM THE SAME
VILLAGE. DID YOU KNOW THAT?

28:30.370 --> 28:32.361
WE BELIEVE
THEY HAVE INSTRUCTIONS

28:32.410 --> 28:35.174
TO GO INTO TOMORROW'S MEETING
AND SABOTAGE YOUR CHANCES

28:35.210 --> 28:37.007
OF ACQUIRING THE WEAPONS
YOU NEED.

28:37.040 --> 28:39.349
THAT IS NOT POSSIBLE.
NO?

28:39.380 --> 28:42.508
ABDUL QADER'S SONS
WERE FIGHTING IN SAYGHANI.

28:42.550 --> 28:44.245
THEY WERE CAPTURED BY SOVIETS.

28:44.290 --> 28:46.508
HE'S LOYAL TO HIS FAMILY,
NOT AFGHANISTAN.

28:46.550 --> 28:48.359
HE AND MOMAND HAVE BEEN
DELIVERING INFORMATION

28:48.390 --> 28:50.517
TO A SOVIET GENERAL
NAMED YASHKIN.

28:50.560 --> 28:52.187
WHY DO YOU THINK THERE'S
BEEN NO FIGHTING

28:52.230 --> 28:54.528
IN HAJI SATAR OR RAHIM?

28:54.560 --> 28:56.198
YOU THINK
THAT'S COINCIDENCE?

28:56.230 --> 28:58.698
WE WENT TO THE CHAIRMAN
OF THE COMMITTEE AND TOLD HIM.

28:58.730 --> 29:00.527
HE SAID WE BROUGHT THEM
ALL THIS WAY.

29:00.570 --> 29:02.037
THE COMMITTEE'S GONNA
LISTEN TO THEM.

29:02.070 --> 29:03.697
YOUR FRIENDS ONLY HAVE TO ACT
LIKE THEY HAVE GOALS

29:03.740 --> 29:06.436
OTHER THAN WINNING THIS WAR,
ALLIES OTHER THAN US,

29:06.470 --> 29:08.279
AND THAT WOULD BE IT.

29:12.580 --> 29:16.778
WHY IS THERE NO WAR HERE...
IN AMERICA?

29:19.120 --> 29:21.588
MY COUNTRY IS ALWAYS
AT WAR.

29:21.620 --> 29:24.418
AND FOR WHAT?
AFGHANISTAN HAS NOTHING.

29:24.460 --> 29:27.384
NO PLANES, NO HELICOPTERS,
NO MEDICINE.

29:27.430 --> 29:30.888
NOTHING OF OUR OWN.

29:30.930 --> 29:32.227
ALL WE WANT IS TO LIVE

29:32.270 --> 29:34.067
ON THE LAND OF OUR FATHERS
IN PEACE.

29:34.100 --> 29:36.739
WE UNDERSTAND.

29:36.770 --> 29:38.465
YOU'RE RIGHT.

29:38.510 --> 29:43.402
I DON'T KNOW THESE MEN.
MY MEN ARE IN THE MOUNTAINS.

29:43.440 --> 29:45.442
MY MEN ARE HONORABLE.

29:45.480 --> 29:49.109
THEY WANT TO FIGHT AND DIE
AS MARTYRS.

29:49.150 --> 29:53.314
DO YOU KNOW THAT A MARTYR
MAY BE LAID IN HIS GRAVE

29:53.350 --> 29:55.489
JUST AS HE DIES?

29:55.520 --> 30:00.457
HIS BODY AND CLOTHES
SOAKED IN BLOOD?

30:00.490 --> 30:05.427
EVEN A PROPHET MUST BE CLEANED
BEFORE BURIAL,

30:05.470 --> 30:07.768
BUT NOT A MARTYR.

30:07.800 --> 30:10.689
SO GREAT IS HIS HONOR.

30:13.140 --> 30:16.632
BUT A TRAITOR...
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

30:16.680 --> 30:20.138
THERE IS A WAY
FOR TOMORROW TO WORK OUT.

30:21.980 --> 30:24.847
IF YOU WERE TO GO
TO THE MEETING ALONE...

30:29.720 --> 30:31.187
TELL ME.

30:31.230 --> 30:36.623
WHAT DOES YOUR INTELLIGENCE
SAY ABOUT ME?

30:36.660 --> 30:39.823
THAT YOU ARE LOYAL,

30:39.870 --> 30:43.067
THAT THERE ARE NO MUJAHIDEEN
AS BRAVE AS YOURS.

30:45.870 --> 30:48.532
I AM ABASSIN ZADRAN.

30:48.580 --> 30:53.700
I AM THE ONE WHO CUTS
THE THROATS OF THE COMMUNISTS.

30:53.750 --> 30:57.379
I HAVE KILLED MANY PEOPLE
WITH MY KNIFE.

30:57.420 --> 31:01.151
I HAVE CUT THEM OPEN
AND WATCHED THEM DIE,

31:01.190 --> 31:02.987
SOME OF THEM BOYS,

31:03.020 --> 31:05.329
NO OLDER THAN MY NEPHEW.

31:05.360 --> 31:10.491
I FOUND THEM SWIMMING,
THEIR GUNS ON THE RIVERBANK,

31:10.530 --> 31:13.567
LAUGHING, SINGING,

31:13.600 --> 31:16.068
AFTER DROPPING BOMBS
ON OUR VILLAGES,

31:16.100 --> 31:20.867
DESECRATING OUR WOMEN,
KILLING OUR BABIES.

31:20.910 --> 31:22.377
THEY'RE COWARDS.

31:25.550 --> 31:31.216
IF THERE WERE 200 INFIDELS
STANDING ON THE ROAD,

31:31.250 --> 31:36.552
I WOULD GUT EVERY ONE OF THEM
LIKE A GOAT.

31:51.970 --> 31:55.576
14 TYPES OF OMELETS,
20 KINDS OF HAMBURGERS.

31:55.610 --> 31:56.872
HOW DOES ONE CHOOSE?

31:56.910 --> 31:58.878
THE PARADOX
OF BEING AMERICAN.

31:58.910 --> 32:01.470
HMM. ISN'T THIS
A GREEK DINER?

32:05.750 --> 32:07.547
[ SIGHS ]
THE RISK WE RUN NOW

32:07.590 --> 32:09.888
IS THINGS WITH PAIGE
WILL MOVE TOO SLOWLY.

32:09.920 --> 32:12.229
PHILIP WILL CONTINUE
TO BLOCK PROGRESS.

32:12.260 --> 32:16.219
WELL, I CAN'T HELP WONDERING
IF PHILIP IS RIGHT.

32:16.260 --> 32:18.091
IT'S THEIR DAUGHTER.

32:19.970 --> 32:21.961
I'M THINKING, CLAUDIA.

32:22.000 --> 32:26.107
I CAN THINK OUT LOUD
WITH YOU AFTER 30 YEARS.

32:26.140 --> 32:30.406
THINK OUT LOUD
ALL YOU LIKE.

32:30.440 --> 32:32.408
IT'S A FREE COUNTRY.

32:32.450 --> 32:34.441
OR HAVEN'T YOU HEARD?

32:36.620 --> 32:38.941
I'M JUST NOT CERTAIN
IT'S THE RIGHT THING.

32:38.990 --> 32:41.254
FOR PAIGE?

32:41.290 --> 32:43.258
NO,
FOR PHILIP AND ELIZABETH.

32:43.290 --> 32:46.748
SHE WAS MUCH BETTER WITH HIM
BEFORE THIS ALL CAME OUT.

32:46.790 --> 32:50.157
WHAT CAN I GET YOU?
I'LL HAVE TEA.

32:50.200 --> 32:52.259
OKAY, WE HAVE, UH, CHAMOMILE,
EARL GREY --

32:52.300 --> 32:54.598
JUST TEA. HOT TEA.

32:54.640 --> 32:57.791
THE SAME.
ALL RIGHT, THANKS.

32:59.710 --> 33:01.803
[ BELL DINGS ]

33:03.180 --> 33:05.478
STARTING TO WISH
YOU DIDN'T COME BACK?

33:06.810 --> 33:08.141
WELL...

33:08.180 --> 33:11.638
IT WAS VERY DULL
IN SERGACH.

33:15.720 --> 33:17.153
WHAT HAPPENED AT THE CENTRE

33:17.190 --> 33:19.681
WHEN THEY HEARD IT WAS THE BOY
WHO KILLED HIS FAMILY?

33:21.230 --> 33:23.790
[ SIGHS ] HONESTLY...

33:23.830 --> 33:28.199
I'D NEVER SEEN ANYTHING
QUITE LIKE IT IN 40 YEARS.

33:28.240 --> 33:31.164
THEY FIRED THE HEAD
OF THE AMERICAN DEPARTMENT,

33:31.210 --> 33:33.667
WHO LEFT IN SHAME.

33:33.710 --> 33:36.031
EVERYONE WAS IN MOURNING.

33:37.380 --> 33:40.178
I THOUGHT THEY MIGHT SHUT DOWN
DIRECTORATE "S."

33:42.850 --> 33:45.512
AND YET WITH ALL THAT...

33:45.550 --> 33:49.259
THEY STILL
WANT TO TRY IT AGAIN?

33:51.860 --> 33:54.420
THEY THINK YOU CAN DO IT.

34:10.080 --> 34:12.002
I NEED TO SPEAK
WITH MY FRIENDS.

34:12.050 --> 34:13.699
MM-HMM.

34:23.060 --> 34:25.119
[ KNOCKS ]

34:27.430 --> 34:29.898
[ SPEAKING PASHTO ]

34:32.230 --> 34:34.095
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

34:43.280 --> 34:44.599
[ SIGHS ]

34:44.650 --> 34:46.277
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

34:51.320 --> 34:54.209
[ MEN SCREAMING, SCUFFLING ]

34:54.260 --> 34:57.479
BRAD! BRAD!

35:02.100 --> 35:03.419
[ DOOR RATTLES ]

35:18.010 --> 35:20.478
DROP IT. NOW.

35:34.460 --> 35:37.452
[ SPEAKING RUSSIAN ]

36:03.160 --> 36:06.152
"GOT PLANS?

36:06.190 --> 36:07.953
"MY HUSBAND WANTS
TO SEE THIS MOVIE,

36:07.990 --> 36:10.652
'THE KING OF COMEDY.'"

36:12.530 --> 36:14.964
"WHAT'S THAT?"

36:15.000 --> 36:16.638
"SOME JERRY LEWIS MOVIE."

36:16.670 --> 36:18.308
"OH, MAN."

36:18.340 --> 36:20.228
"RIGHT?"

36:58.040 --> 37:00.406
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

37:00.450 --> 37:02.418
COME IN.

37:19.900 --> 37:21.094
[ CLICK, RADIO TURNS ON ]

37:21.130 --> 37:23.394
[ ULTRAVOX'S "VIENNA" PLAYING ]

37:23.440 --> 37:24.862
* THE WARMTH OF YOUR HAND
AND A COLD GRAY SKY *

37:24.910 --> 37:28.277
* IT FADES TO A DISTANCE

37:28.310 --> 37:31.438
***

37:31.480 --> 37:33.038
PAIGE...

37:33.080 --> 37:38.074
I'M GOING TO SEE MY MOTHER
BEFORE SHE DIES...

37:38.120 --> 37:40.645
IN RUSSIA.

37:42.290 --> 37:46.886
* THIS MEANS NOTHING TO ME

37:46.930 --> 37:51.390
I TALKED IT OVER WITH DAD.

37:51.430 --> 37:54.069
WE THINK YOU SHOULD GO
WITH ME.

37:54.100 --> 37:56.762
IT WOULD BE THE ONLY CHANCE
YOU'LL HAVE

37:56.800 --> 37:58.438
TO MEET YOUR GRANDMOTHER.

37:58.470 --> 38:01.268
***

38:01.310 --> 38:04.404
BUT IT'S YOUR CHOICE.

38:04.450 --> 38:09.274
***

38:09.320 --> 38:13.939
* THIS MEANS NOTHING TO ME

38:15.360 --> 38:20.957
* THIS MEANS NOTHING TO ME

38:20.990 --> 38:25.962
* OH, VIENNA

38:26.000 --> 38:29.333
MARTHA?

38:29.370 --> 38:32.134
MAR--

38:32.170 --> 38:35.469
***

38:42.650 --> 38:45.778
I'M SORRY, CLARK.
I, UH...

38:45.820 --> 38:48.459
MARTHA,
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

38:48.490 --> 38:50.310
TO MY PARENTS'.

38:50.360 --> 38:52.157
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

38:52.190 --> 38:53.657
I NEED A BREAK.

38:53.690 --> 38:55.191
WE NEED A BREAK.

38:55.230 --> 38:57.118
MARTHA --
NO, UM...

38:57.160 --> 39:01.119
I CAN'T TAKE IT.

39:01.170 --> 39:03.297
[Voice breaking ] EVERYONE
AT WORK KNOWS THAT I'M LYING.

39:03.340 --> 39:05.968
NO, NO, THEY DON'T.
WHEN I COME HOME, YOU'RE NOT...
[ SNIFFLES ]

39:06.010 --> 39:08.706
MARTHA, I KNOW HOW HARD
THIS IS.

39:08.740 --> 39:11.743
I KNOW, BUT I AM TRYING.

39:13.550 --> 39:15.472
I KNOW YOU ARE.

39:15.520 --> 39:18.011
BUT IT'S NOT ENOUGH.

39:19.250 --> 39:21.309
I'M SORRY, CLARK,
BUT IT'S --

39:21.350 --> 39:22.510
IT'S NOT ENOUGH.

39:22.560 --> 39:25.028
[ SNIFFLES ]
THEY'RE NOT GONNA LET UP

39:25.060 --> 39:28.393
UNTIL THEY FIND THE PERSON
THAT PUT THAT PEN THERE.

39:28.430 --> 39:31.354
I-I AM WORKING ON IT,
AND I WILL FIGURE IT OUT.

39:31.400 --> 39:33.163
I PROMISE.

39:33.200 --> 39:35.168
I AM WITH YOU.

39:35.200 --> 39:38.033
MARTHA, I-I-I LOVE YOU.

39:38.070 --> 39:40.709
I LOVE YOU. YOU...

39:40.740 --> 39:42.571
I'M YOUR HUSBAND.

39:42.610 --> 39:45.170
[ EXHALES ]

39:45.210 --> 39:46.848
[ SNIFFLES ]

39:46.880 --> 39:50.008
WHATEVER KIND OF ARRANGEMENT
YOU WANT IS FINE. UM...

39:50.050 --> 39:53.838
I LET YOU IN HERE.
IT'S FINE.

39:53.890 --> 39:55.380
I JUST... [ SNIFFLES ]

39:56.720 --> 39:59.188
WHEN MY MOTHER ASKS,
I DON'T EVEN KNOW WHAT TO SAY.

39:59.230 --> 40:00.857
[ SNIFFLES ]

40:00.890 --> 40:02.528
AND IT'S NOT JUST THAT.
IT'S...

40:02.560 --> 40:04.528
[ SNIFFLES ]

40:04.570 --> 40:09.735
I CAN'T BE HERE WITH YOU
LIKE THIS.

40:12.310 --> 40:16.906
[ SNIFFLES ]

40:16.940 --> 40:20.740
[ SIGHS ]

40:22.580 --> 40:25.879
I WAS 18 WHEN I LEFT,

40:25.920 --> 40:28.081
AND I ALWAYS TOLD MY MOTHER
TO TURN MY ROOM

40:28.120 --> 40:32.227
INTO A SEWING ROOM,
YOU KNOW? [ SNIFFLES ]

40:32.260 --> 40:34.228
BUT SHE WOULDN'T DO IT.

40:34.260 --> 40:37.593
SHE JUST WOULDN'T DO IT.
[ SNIFFLES ]

40:39.970 --> 40:42.097
[ SNIFFLES ]
MARTHA...

41:11.500 --> 41:14.537
[ GLASSES AND PINS CLATTER ]

41:47.830 --> 41:56.169
[ ADHESIVE TEARING ]

41:57.710 --> 41:59.177
[ GASPS ]

42:07.350 --> 42:11.855
[ PINS CLATTERING ]

42:20.600 --> 42:22.261
[ GASPS ]
